/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.POLICY_NAME is 'Name of Fine Grained Auditing Policy'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.NEW_OWNER is 'Owner of the object named in the NEW_NAME column'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.NEW_NAME is 'New name of object after RENAME, or name of underlying object (e.g. CREATE INDEX owner.obj_name ON new_owner.new_name)'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.ACTION is 'Numeric action type code'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.STATEMENT_TYPE is 'Action type corresponding to the numeric code in ACTION'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.AUDIT_OPTION is 'Auditing option set with the standard audit statement'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.TRANSACTIONID is 'Transaction identifier of the transaction in which the object is accessed or modified'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.RETURNCODE is 'Oracle error code generated by the action. Zero if the action succeeded'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.SCN is 'SCN (System Change Number) of the query'
/

comment on column SYS.DBA_COMMON_AUDIT_TRAIL.COMMENT_TEXT is 'Text comment on the audit trail entry.
Also indicates how the user was authenticated. The method can be one of the
following:
1. "DATABASE" - authentication was done by password.
2. "NETWORK"  - authentication was done by Net8 or the Advanced Networking
   Option.
3. "PROXY"    - the client was authenticated by another user. The name of the
   proxy user follows the method type.'
/

